<div class="text-center custom-orange-bg">
  <div class="d-flex justify-content-center custom-orange-bg">
    <div class="col-12 col-md-10 col-lg-8 mb-5 custom-orange-bg"> <!-- Full width on mobile, smaller on larger screens -->
      <br/>
      <h1><%= @workout_routine.name %></h1>
      <br/>
      <%= link_to 'New Exercise', new_workout_routine_exercise_path(@workout_routine), class: 'btn btn-primary' %>

      <div class="container-fluid mt-5"> <!-- Use container-fluid for better responsiveness -->
        <div class="table-responsive"> <!-- Ensures horizontal scrolling for the table -->
          <table class="table table-striped table-bordered mt-3 bg-light">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Exercise</th>
                <th>Reps</th>
                <th>Sets</th>
                <th>Weight</th>
                <th>Volume</th>
                <th>Completed</th>
                <th>Actions</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <% @workout_routine.exercises.each do |exercise| %>
                <tr>
                  <td><%= exercise.name %></td>
                  <td><%= exercise.reps %></td>
                  <td><%= exercise.sets %></td>
                  <td><%= exercise.weight %></td>
                  <td><%= exercise.reps * exercise.sets * exercise.weight %> lbs</td>
                  <td>
                    <input type="checkbox" class="exercise-checkbox" data-routine-id="<%= @workout_routine.id %>">
                  </td>
                  <td>
                    <%= link_to 'Show', [@workout_routine, exercise], class: 'btn btn-secondary' %>
                    <%= link_to 'Edit', edit_workout_routine_exercise_path(@workout_routine, exercise), class: 'btn btn-warning' %>
                    <%= link_to 'Destroy', [@workout_routine, exercise], method: :delete, data: { confirm: 'Are you sure?' }, class: 'btn btn-danger' %>
                  </td>
                </tr>
              <% end %>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <p><strong>Mood:</strong> <%= @workout_routine.mood %></p>
          <p><strong>Sleep Quality:</strong> <%= @workout_routine.sleep_quality %></p>
          <p><strong>Soreness:</strong> <%= @workout_routine.soreness %></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="container mt-5">
        <h1>Total Volume Lifted: <%= @workout_routine.total_volume %> lbs</h1>
      </div>

      <div class="container mt-5">
       <div class="container mt-5">
        <div class="card aggressive-burnout shadow-lg">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h2 class="card-title text-danger fw-bold">🔥 Burnout Metrics</h2>
          <p><strong>Acute Load:</strong> <%= @workout_routine.acute_load %> lbs</p>
          <p><strong>Chronic Load:</strong> <%= @workout_routine.chronic_load %> lbs</p>
          <p><strong>ACWR:</strong> <%= @workout_routine.acwr.round(2) %></p>
          <p class="text-muted small">
            Acute:Chronic Workload Ratio — compares your short-term (1 week) load to long-term (4 weeks) load. 
            Helps you avoid overtraining by identifying rapid spikes in activity.
          </p>

          <p><strong>Training Stress Balance (TSB):</strong> <%= @workout_routine.tsb %> lbs</p>
          <p class="text-muted small">
            Training Stress Balance reflects your recovery state — it’s the difference between your chronic and acute load.
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>✅ Positive TSB:</strong> You’re well-rested and ready to go.</li>
            <li><strong>⚠️ Negative TSB:</strong> Fatigue is building, monitor closely.</li>
            <li><strong>🚨 Very Negative TSB:</strong> High risk of burnout or injury — rest advised!</li>
          </ul>

          <p><strong>🔥 Burnout Risk Score:</strong> <%= @workout_routine.calculate_burnout_risk_score %></p>
          <p class="text-muted small">
            Burnout Risk Score is based on a combination of ACWR, TSB, and load trends. The higher the number, the more likely you are to be overtrained or fatigued.
          </p>

          <p><strong>🚦 ACWR Status:</strong> <%= @workout_routine.acwr_status %></p>
          <p class="text-muted small">
            ACWR Status is determined by how your ratio compares to safe training thresholds.
          </p>

          <hr>
          <h5>📊 ACWR Interpretation Scale:</h5>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Below 0.8:</strong> Undertraining — minimal performance gains.</li>
            <li><strong>0.8 to 1.3:</strong> Safe Zone — optimal balance of load and recovery.</li>
            <li><strong>1.3 to 1.5:</strong> Elevated Risk — performance may improve, but watch for fatigue.</li>
            <li><strong>Above 1.5:</strong> Danger Zone — high risk of injury or burnout.</li>
          </ul>

          <h5>🔥 Burnout Risk Score Scale:</h5>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>0–3:</strong> Low Risk — continue training as planned.</li>
            <li><strong>4–6:</strong> Moderate Risk — monitor recovery and adjust if needed.</li>
            <li><strong>7–8:</strong> High Risk — reduce load and prioritize rest.</li>
            <li><strong>9–10:</strong> Critical — immediate rest required to avoid injury or overtraining.</li>
          </ul>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <%= link_to 'Back', workout_routines_path, class: 'btn btn-secondary' %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
